---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';

export const prerender = true;

const title = "Privacy Policy | ExpatBuildr";
const description = "Transparency on how we handle your data, advertising pixels, and payments.";
---

<Layout 
    title={title}
    description={description}
>
    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-12 px-6">
        <header class="mb-16 reveal-on-scroll">
            <p class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.4em] text-accent-blue mb-4">
                Institutional / Documentation / Legal
            </p>
            <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-8xl font-black font-display tracking-tighter leading-none mb-6 text-slate-900 dark:text-white uppercase">
                PRIVACY<br/>
                <span class="text-slate-900/20 dark:text-white/20">POLICY.</span>
            </h1>
            <p class="text-slate-500 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest">Last Updated: July 7, 2026</p>
        </header>

        <div class="prose">

            <section class="space-y-4">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase tracking-tight pb-2 border-b-2 border-slate-900/10 dark:border-white/10">01 · Overview</h2>
                <p>
                    At ExpatBuildr, we believe in transparency. This policy outlines how we collect, use, and share your information when you visit our site, read the blog, download a free resource, subscribe to the Galaxy Arbitrage Newsletter, or purchase a digital product.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase tracking-tight pb-2 border-b-2 border-slate-900/10 dark:border-white/10">02 · Information We Collect</h2>
                <div class="space-y-6">
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg">A. Email Subscriptions (Beehiiv)</h3>
                        <p>
                            When you subscribe to the Galaxy Arbitrage Newsletter or unlock gated content, your email address is processed and stored via <strong>Beehiiv</strong>. We use this to send you the newsletter, digital product delivery, and promotional content. You can opt out at any time via the unsubscribe link in the footer of our emails.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg">B. Payment Data (Stripe)</h3>
                        <p>
                            When you purchase a digital product or service, payments are processed securely via <strong>Stripe</strong>. ExpatBuildr does not store your credit card information on our servers. Stripe's privacy policy applies to these transactions.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase tracking-tight pb-2 border-b-2 border-slate-900/10 dark:border-white/10">03 · Advertising Pixels & Data Shared With Ad Platforms</h2>
                <p>
                    <strong>We share information about your visit and, in some cases, your email address with advertising platforms.</strong> We do this to measure whether our ads are working and to show our content and offers to people similar to our existing audience. Specifically:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600">
                    <li><strong>Meta (Facebook/Instagram) Pixel & Conversions API:</strong> Shares page views, button clicks, and — when you submit a form — a hashed (encrypted) version of your email address, so Meta can match the event to an ad account and build retargeting and lookalike audiences.</li>
                    <li><strong>TikTok Pixel:</strong> Shares page views and conversion events (such as completing a purchase or signup) with TikTok Ads.</li>
                    <li><strong>Reddit Pixel:</strong> Shares page visits and lead events, and — using Reddit's Advanced Matching — a hashed version of your email address when you subscribe or convert.</li>
                    <li><strong>LinkedIn Insight Tag:</strong> Shares page views and conversion events with LinkedIn Ads, primarily for B2B and professional-audience retargeting.</li>
                    <li><strong>X (Twitter) Pixel:</strong> Shares page views and lead events with X Ads.</li>
                    <li><strong>Google Analytics (GA4) & Google Ads:</strong> Shares traffic and conversion data to help us understand how visitors use the site and measure ad performance.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    Each of these platforms may combine the data we send with other data they already hold about you (from their own apps or other sites you've visited) according to their own privacy policies. We do not sell your data — this sharing is solely to operate and measure our own advertising. You can limit this by using your browser's tracking protections, an ad blocker, or by opting out directly through each platform's ad settings (for example, Meta's Ad Preferences, Google's Ad Settings, or the equivalent settings on TikTok, Reddit, LinkedIn, and X).
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase tracking-tight pb-2 border-b-2 border-slate-900/10 dark:border-white/10">04 · Data Usage</h2>
                <p>
                    We use your data to:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-gray-600 font-medium">
                    <li>Deliver the newsletter, digital downloads, and products you request.</li>
                    <li>Process payments for products and services you purchase.</li>
                    <li>Measure and improve the performance of our advertising across the platforms listed above.</li>
                    <li>Understand site traffic and content performance so we can improve the blog and products.</li>
                    <li>Communicate important updates about your subscription, purchase, or account access.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-black uppercase tracking-tight pb-2 border-b-2 border-slate-900/10 dark:border-white/10">05 · Contact</h2>
                <p>
                    If you have questions about your data, want to opt out of ad tracking, or wish to request deletion of your record, please contact us at:
                </p>
                <a href="mailto:privacy@expatbuildr.com" class="inline-block font-black border-b-2 border-accent-blue pb-1 hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors no-underline">
                    privacy@expatbuildr.com
                </a>
            </section>

        </div>

        <div class="mt-24 pt-8 border-t border-slate-900/10 dark:border-white/10 flex justify-between items-center text-[10px] font-mono text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest">
            <span>© {new Date().getFullYear()} ExpatBuildr</span>
            <a href="/terms" class="hover:text-accent-blue transition-colors">Go to Terms of Service →</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>
